name: Musa
description: Musa, known as Teamoza, was the queen of the Parthian Empire from 2 BC to 4 AD. Originally a Roman slave girl, she was given as a gift by the Roman emperor Augustus (reigned from 27 BC to 14 AD) to Farhad IV, Parthian king (reigned from 37 to 2 BC). She quickly climbed the ladder and became the queen and wife of Farhad IV and gave birth to Farhadak (Farhad V). He then poisoned Farhad IV in 2 BC and, along with Farhad V, ruled the empire.
